CITY AND COUNTY OF SAN FRANCISCO
BOARD OF SUPERVISORS
CLERK'S OFFICE
ROOM 235 CITY HALL
February 24, 1928.
Hon. John 0 Toole, City Attorney,
City Hall,
San Francisco.
Dear Sir:
By direction of Supervisor Milo F. Kent I am trans-
mitting herewith report of the City Engineer and correspondence
relative to
bill of Millbrae Dairy
in the sum of
$1531 for cutting grass at the Mills Field Municipal Airport.
This work was
never authorized by the Airport Com-
nor were requisitions ever issued for
the work,
you will see by
the report of the City Engineer, a misunder-
standing exists as to whether the City was to be put to any
expense
in connection with the cutting of the grass.
that the work was never formally authorized,
Airport Committee feels that the bill is exorbitant and,
there-
fore,
requests you to get in touch with the Millbrae Dairy
Company and see if by negotiations with them you cannot arrange
for a compromise in the amount of this bill.
Kindly return the City Engineer's letter and
the
other
correspondence with your report on the result
your negotia-
tions.
Yours very truly,
JWR :H
